## How to Delete Files in a Directory Excluding some Files

Sometimes you'll want to delete many files from a directory without deleting some other files. Thus, deleting these one after the other can be sterssfull and annoying
Here is a simple way of doing this on any linux distributon with just a simple command

### Example
Run the following command to delete all files in ```shell .```  (the current directory) except ```mysql.sock```
``` shell
 find . ! -name 'mysql.sock' -type f -exec rm -f {} +
 ```
 
 

Have fun with system admin!!!
